# Auth & Authorization

All authentication is handled by Clerk. Every server-side data access must be scoped to the authenticated user — never expose or mutate another user's data.

## Getting the Current User

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — Server Component or Route Handler
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

// ✅ GOOD — Server Action
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

export async function myAction() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) return { error: "Unauthorized" };
  // ...
}
```

## Scoping Queries to the Authenticated User

Always filter by `clerkUserId` when querying user-owned resources.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const userDecks = await db
  .select()
  .from(decks)
  .where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));

// ❌ BAD — missing ownership check
const allDecks = await db.select().from(decks);
```

## Verifying Ownership Before Mutations

Before updating or deleting a resource, verify the record belongs to the current user.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const deck = await db.query.decks.findFirst({
  where: and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)),
});
if (!deck) throw new Error("Not found");

await db.delete(decks).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));

// ❌ BAD — deletes by id alone, no ownership check
await db.delete(decks).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));
```

## Rules

- Always call `auth()` at the top of every server action, route handler, and data-fetching function
- Always return a 401/redirect or throw early if `userId` is null
- Never trust client-supplied user IDs — always derive the userId from `auth()`
- Never skip ownership checks when accessing nested resources (e.g. cards inherit ownership from their deck)
